    • Method Detail

      • onDisconnectionRequested

        void onDisconnectionRequested(TNTBLEPeripheral peripheral,
                            int deviceStatus,
                            int error)
        Invoked when the app requests disconnection to peripheral.

        After this method is invoked, the app is disconnected to peripheral by TNTBLEManager.cancelConnection().

        Parameters:
        peripheral - The peripheral that has been disconnected.
        deviceStatus - The status of disconnected peripheral.(Refer to TNTDeviceStatus.)
        error - The cause of the failure.(Refer to TNTBLEError)

      • onUUIDSaved

               int result,
               int deviceStatus,
               int error)
        Invoked when the UUID has been saved to peripheral.

        Parameters:
        peripheral - The peripheral that has been saved UUID.
        result - The result that app saves applicationUUID to peripheral.
        deviceStatus - The status of peripheral(Refer to TNTDeviceStatus).
        error - The cause of the failure.(Refer to TNTBLEError.)

      • onUserInformationSaved

        void onUserInformationSaved(TNTBLEPeripheral peripheral,
                          TNTUserInformation userInformation,
                          int deviceStatus,
                          int error)
        Invoked when the user information is saved to peripheral.
        Parameters:
        peripheral - The peripheral that have been saved user information.
        userInformation - The user information that have been saved to peripheral.
        notice : peripheral returns newer one which compares registration date between app just saved and peripheral already retained.
        deviceStatus - The status of peripheral(Refer to TNTDeviceStatus).
        error - The cause of the failure.(Refer to TNTBLEError.)
